fr.inria.atlanmod.mogwai.util

Class TransformationHelper

  • Object
    • TransformationHelper

  • public class TransformationHelper
extends Object
    A helper used in generated script to execute transformation-related instructions.

    The methods provided in this class are called by the transformation to avoid complex (and inefficient) gremlin instructions. This helper is independent of the implicit schema used to represent the model, and delegate all the graph database accesses to its embedded EMFtoGraphMapping.

    Author:
    Gwendal DANIEL
    See Also:
    EMFtoGraphMapping

      • createElement

        public Vertex createElement(Vertex source,
                            String targetLabel,
                            String metaclassType,
                            String nsURI,
                            String resourceName)
        Creates a new element mapped from the provided source.

        The source element and the targetLabel are provided to allow trace link creation. Element creation is delegated to the underlying EMFtoGraphMapping, that processes the metaclassType and nsURI to create a new instance of the given type.

        Parameters:
        source - the element mapped by the transformation
        targetLabel - the label used in the transformation for the created element
        metaclassType - the type of the element to create
        nsURI - the uri of the EPackage containing the metaclass to instantiate
        Returns:
        the created Vertex
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the provided metaclassType is null

        Note: isContainment parameter is used by the underlying EMFtoGraphMapping to store container specific information

        Parameters:

        v2 - the head Vertex
        label - the label of the link
        isContainment - true if the link is a containment, false otherwise
        Returns:
        the created Edge

        NullPointerException - if v1, v2, or label is null

      • resolve

        public Vertex resolve(Vertex source)
        Resolves the source Vertex by inspecting trace links.

        This method returns the Vertex linked to source by a trace link if it exists. This allows to handle multiple reference of the same element in the ATL transformation.

        Parameters:
        source - the Vertex to resolve
        Returns:
        the Vertex corresponding to the resolved element

      • linkReference

        public Edge linkReference(Vertex source,
                          Vertex target,
                          String label,
                          boolean isContainment)
        Links two elements by creating an edge between the corresponding Vertex elements.

        Note that target is an element in the source model that has to be resolved. If target cannot be resolved (because the corresponding Vertex has not been created yet) a proxy link (see GraphHelper#pLink(Vertex, Vertex, String)) is created that will be resolved later.

        Parameters:
        source - the tail of the link
        target - a source element that is resolved and set as the head of the link. If it cannot be resolved a proxy link is created instead
        label - the label of the link
        isContainment - true if the reference is a containment, false otherwise
        Returns:
        the created Edge
        See Also:
        #linkReference(Vertex, Iterable, String)

      • linkReference

        public List<Edge> linkReference(Vertex source,
                                Iterable<Vertex> target,
                                String label,
                                boolean isContainment)
        Links all the elements of target to source by creating edges between the corresponding Vertex elements.

        Note that target contains elements in the source model that have to be resolved. If targetÂ elements cannot be resolved (because corresponding Vertex have not been created yet) a proxy link (see GraphHelper#pLink(Vertex, Vertex, String)) is created that will be resolved later.

        Parameters:
        source - the tail of the links
        target - a GremlinGroovyPipeline containing the elements that have to be resolved and set as the head of the created links. If some of them cannot be resolved a proxy link is created instead
        label - the label of the link
        isContainment - true if the reference is a containment, false otherwise
        Returns:
        a list containing the created Edges
        See Also:
        #linkReference(Vertex, Vertex, String)
